        "content": "<p>Yeah, I believe that. But since we already have gradient well-defined for an inner-product space, the task left is just to show divergence is well-defined for an inner-product space as well, and then we can compose them. Not to say that a direct approach is worse in any way.</p>",
        "id": 447490412,
